Bintangkechil wrote a review Dec 2019
Singapore, Singapore737 contributions157 helpful votes
Near the beach
Located just across the beach, the hotel offers a good view of the sea at the rooftop. The rooftop swimming pool is a nice place to chill. It can get quite cold in December though. The room is huge.It has a nice kitchenette with a microwave. The room is dim though. Brighter lighting will be perfect. As my room doesn’t face the sea, I feel a little claustrophobic. The problem is solved by opening the window. Staff are polite and professional. More human touch will be nice. Definitely will recommend to others. The price is also reasonable.
Date of stay: December 2019
